Senior Web Engineer, BLX
BLX Group LLC provides tax compliance, financial advisory, and investment advisory services to governmental and non-profit organizations. We’ve been serving the municipal finance industry since 1989, helping clients manage their tax-exempt bond financings from original conception to final redemption.

BLX is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Orrick, Herrington & Sutcliffe LLP, a global law firm recognized by Fortune as one of the “100 Best Companies to Work For” and the Financial Times as the “Most Innovative Law Firm in North America.”

BLX is looking for Senior Web Engineers to build the foundation of our new digital operations team, which will become a key part of our business as our industry evolves. As an engineer at BLX, you’ll be working on new web-based systems to streamline our internal operations and contribute to the digital transformation of municipal finance.

Essential Position Responsibilities:
•	Build and iterate on financial analysis systems that will become key to BLX’s operations
•	Be a core contributor to the design and architecture of those systems
•	Help develop coding, review, and test standards
•	Collaborate with other members of the team and business stakeholders
Knowledge, Experience, and Education:

•	4+ years software engineering experience
•	Experience working on small, agile, teams
•	Strong proficiency in PHP, SQL, HTML, CSS, and JavaScript
•	Familiarity with JavaScript frameworks (such as React or Vue.js) is a plus
•	Good communication skills
•	Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or equivalent experience
Benefits/Perks:

•	Comprehensive benefits package including paid time-off, health, dental, vision, life, and retirement
•	Paid parking or public transportation passes
•	Daily catered lunch
How to Apply:
To submit your resume and cover letter for this position, please select the Apply For This Job option at the top of the page. The submission form will require a cover letter. Feel free to make it brief. Your experience on your resume is what we what to see!

No direct phone calls or emails please.

All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, sex, color, religion, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, protected veteran status, or on the basis of disability.

Qualified applicants with criminal histories will be considered for the position in a manner consistent with the requirements of the Los Angeles Fair Chance Initiative for Hiring.